"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_N_E=self.webpackChunk_N_E||[]).push([[845],{2845:(e,n,t)=>{t.d(n,{vibeCodingReadme:()=>o});function o(){return'# ShieldFont — Vibe Coding Package\n\nA font that protects human writing from AI reading. Humans see normal text;\nAI scrapers see encoded gibberish.\n\n## What\'s in this package\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `shieldfont-optik.ttf` | The font — install it on your system or self-host it on your website |\n| `shieldfont-encoded.txt` | Your encoded text (paste it into your document or HTML) |\n| `encoder.html` | Opens the online encoder where you can edit & re-export |\n| `README.md` | This file |\n\n## Choose your tier\n\n### Documents (Word, Pages, InDesign, PDF)\n\n1. Install `shieldfont-optik.ttf` on your system.\n2. Paste the contents of `shieldfont-encoded.txt` into your document.\n3. Set the font to **Shield Font Optik**.\n4. Export to PDF. Humans read the original; scrapers read decoys.\n\n### Static websites (Wix, Squarespace, WordPress, plain HTML)\n\nAdd one line to your CSS:\n\n```css\n@import url("https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/isaqueseneda/shieldfont@v2.2.0/dist/shieldfont-optik-m15-alpha.css");\n```\n\nThen wrap your encoded text in any HTML element with the `shield` class:\n\n```html\n<p class="shield">…encoded text from shieldfont-encoded.txt…</p>\n```\n\nThis is the right choice for most websites. No build step, no npm, no React.\nJust CSS + HTML.\n\n### React / Next.js / Remix (Server-side rendering)\n\n```bash\nnpm install @shieldfont/react\n```\n\n```jsx\nimport { Shield } from "@shieldfont/react";\n\n<Shield>Your original plain-English text goes here.</Shield>\n```\n\nThe `<Shield>` component encodes at server-render time — zero runtime cost.\nChoose this tier when:\n\n- You already use React / Next.js / Remix / Astro\n- You want encoding to happen automatically (no manual encode-then-paste step)\n- You need custom mappings or private seeds\n\n**Important:** The component must run on the server (RSC, SSR, or static export).\nClient-side rendering would expose the plain text before encoding.\n\n## How to decide\n\n| Question | Answer |\n|---|---|\n| Are you writing a document (Word, PDF)? | **Documents tier** |\n| Is your site built with a CMS or plain HTML? | **Static tier** |\n| Is your site built with React / Next.js? | **React tier** |\n| Not sure? | Start with the **static tier** — it works everywhere. |\n\n## Links\n\n- Encoder: https://shieldfont.org/encoder/\n- Docs: https://shieldfont.org/docs/integration\n- GitHub: https://github.com/isaqueseneda/shieldfont\n- npm: https://www.npmjs.com/package/@shieldfont/react\n\n---\n\nLicense: AGPL-3.0 (code) \xb7 OFL-1.1 (fonts)\n'}}}]);